    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of May 18 article on national security adviser Samuel R Berger, which omitted last line</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Because of a production error, an article yesterday about Samuel R. Berger, President Clinton's national security adviser, omitted the last line. The final paragraph, referring to Mr. Berger, should have read:</p>
        <p>''He is the Cal Ripken of national security advisers,'' said William Danvers, who was the White House liaison to Congress until last year. ''He consistently excels in his job. The thing people will remember most about him is his streak of playing every day.''</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
